subSubSection.paragraph:
Terminalia
(
Figs 15–17
). Ovipositor long with microtrichia on sternites 6, 7 and 8; cerci short; segments 6 and 7 not fused; 
epiprct
not modified, setulose, about 2x as high as wide; 
hyprct
well developed, somewhat triangular, with four differentiated setae, one in each lateral margin and two apically; tergites 6 and 7 membranous; three rounded spermathecae.
